rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that provides cosmetic treatments and services for men and women, generally focused on hair and skin health and beauty.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beauty Salon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishments that specialize in selling products and services relating to skin care, body care, hair care, and nail care, e.g. cosmetics, makeup, perfumes, and fragrances.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beauty Supply Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling women's garments that are designed to be worn during weddings, e.g. wedding gowns, veils, and related garments and accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bridalwear Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all categories of types of fashion. These are general groupings for fashion, like 'ready to wear' and 'haute couture'
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fashion Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling formal and casual clothing for children.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Children's Clothing Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling items (often decorative) that are worn to complement or enhance garments, e.g. gloves, mittens, hats, scarves, jewelry, watches, and umbrellas.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clothing Accessories Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on a region's typical sizing. For example, the UK has different sizing from the rest of Europe and from the United States.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Regional Clothing Sizing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.clothing_size relationship to the mso:fashion.garment to which the sizing applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Article of Clothing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying a non-numeric modifier of the size. For example, in the case of a 38L suit, L is the notation; in the case of a 34C bra, C is the notation; in the case of an 11EEE shoe, EEE is the notation. Additional values such as 'petite' can also be entered here.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.clothing_sizing relationship to the mso:location.location to which the sizing for the garment type applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Region

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the section of the garment, if any, to which the size information corresponds, e.g. bust, waist, inseam, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Section

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the numeric size. For example, in the case of a 38L suit, enter 38; in the case of a 34C bra, enter 34; in the case of an 11EEE shoe, enter 11.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of measure corresponding to the size of the garment, e.g. inch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that sell items designed to be worn on the human body or to complement one's appearance. Includes clothing accessories, footwear, uniforms, costumes, retailers and manufacturers, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clothing Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling cosmetics, substances used to enhance or protect the appearance of the body, e.g. lotions, powders, lipstick, polishes, makeup, and hair colors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cosmetics Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling garments typically not worn for everyday use, but for amusement, decoration or special events such as holidays, festivals, or performances. See fashion.uniform_store for stores that sell standardized garments worn for work, school or sporting events.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Costume Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all day spas. These businesses provide health and beauty services for patrons. These businesses differ from beauty salons in that they contain facilities like saunas, pools, or whirlpools, and they differ from destination spas in that they do not have overnight guests. Note some destination spas can function as day spas, if patrons are allowed who are not also guests.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day Spa

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fashion designers. These are the people or groups that apply design principles to clothing or accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fashion Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property that relates an mso:fashion.designer to the mso:fashion.designer_label_association relationship that holds the data for a designer's tenure at a particular fashion label.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Labels

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the tenure of a designer with a label.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer-Label Association

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.designer_label_association relationship to the mso:fashion.designer associated with the label.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.designer_label_association relationship to the date the association began.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.designer_label_association relationship to the label with which the designer is or was associated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Label

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.designer_label_associated relationship to the ending date of the association.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail outlets that specialize in selling the raw materials for making clothing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fabric Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on a fashion choice for a given mso:people.person. Data include the source, the designer, and the date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fashion Choice

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.fashion_choice to the mso:fashion.designer that created the piece worn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fibers. Fibers are the slender, elongated material that is used to weave or spin material or yarn. Fiber can be natural, like silk, cotton, and linen, or artificial like rayon or polyester.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fiber

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.fiber to the mso:fashion.textile that the fiber is used to create.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Textiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Outer wear for the feet, including shoes, sandals, boots, and slippers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Footwear

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to a standard indicator for the width of feet that fit the footwear, e.g. M, B, XW, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Foot Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to the height, if any, of the heel in millimeters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heel Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to a textual descriptor of the style of the heel, if any, e.g. padded, stiletto, square, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Heel Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to the material from which the part of the sole that touches the feet is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Insole Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to the material from which the part of the sole that touches the ground is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Outsole Material

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a set of footwear to a textual descriptor of the style of the toe, e.g. rounded toe, pointed toe, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toe Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of apparel, viz. clothing and footwear. Some examples of types of apparel are 'dress', 'hat', and 'swimsuits'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Garment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a garment to a description of the type of closure(s) on the garment, e.g. zippers, buttons, snaps, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Closure Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a garment to the kind of fabric(s) from which the garment is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fabric

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a garment to a descriptor for the kind of fit that the garment has, e.g. slim fit or regular fit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fit Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.garment to another, more specialized garment. For example, the garment 'swimwear' has subtypes of 'one-piece', 'bikini', and 'tankini'
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specialized Garment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: a property that relates a garment to a textual description of any decorative sewing that the garment includes
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Needlework

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a garment to information about the pattern(s) or graphic(s), e.g. geometric, printed on the garment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pattern

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a garment to a description of the style of the pockets on the garment, e.g. two front pockets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pocket Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a garment to information about the size of the garment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a garment to a qualitative descriptor of the size of the garment, e.g. petite, small, medium, extra large, etc. Note that the property mso:fashion.garment.size should be used in cases of sizes that are specified numerically.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a garment to a descriptor for the kind of sleeves that the garment has, e.g. short or full.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sleeve Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.garment to its broader categorization mso:fashion.garment. For example, 'athletic shoe' is a specialization of 'shoe'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specialization Of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in removing body hair for clients.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hair Removal Salon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in providing grooming, cutting and styling services for women's or men's hair, including barbers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hair Salon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail outlets that offer products and services for hair, e.g. preparations for cleaning and beautifying hair, hair loss treatments, hair removal, hair replacement, shampoo, conditioners, wigs, ethnic hair care, hair brushes, hair clips, hair bows, and other hair accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hair Supply Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling bags that are designed to be carried by men or women as a clothing accessory.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Handbag Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling clothing accessories that are designed to cover the top of the head, for fashion or to conserve warmth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hat Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling ornaments, such as bracelets, necklaces, or rings, made of precious metals and often set with gems or imitation gems, as well as small timepieces, especially ones worn on the wrist or carried in the pocket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Jewelry and Watches Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that sell supplies related to techniques and processes associated with creating decorative cloth by needlework out of yarn or string.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Knitting Supply Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fashion labels. These are the distinctive names sewn into the garment and identifying the buyer of the design. Some designers have their own label, others sell to individuals, and others design for design houses or stores.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fashion Label

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:fashion.label to the mso:fashion.designer_label_association relationship that collects the data on a given designer's association with a given label.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling undergarments for women, especially ones that are considered fashionable or alluring.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lingerie Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling women's garments that are designed to be worn during pregnancy and nursing, e.g. breastfeeding clothing and motherhood clothing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maternity Clothing Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling garments designed for men. Includes stores that sell men's accessories (cuff links, hats, ties), casual wear, formal wear, outerwear, shirts, special sizes (big and tall), swimwear, underwear, and retailers and manufacturers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Men's Clothing Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in providing models for advertising and clothing companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Modeling Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A beauty salon that specializes in nail care services such as manicures, pedicures, and nail enhancement.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nail Salon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in printing graphics on materials like textile, wood, plastic, metal or glass
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Screen Printing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in fixing shoes, e.g. resoling shoes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shoe Repair

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling footwear, including boots, athletic shoes, and dress shoes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shoe Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling clothing that is designed to be worn while participating in a sport. Includes cycling, equestrian, golf, ski, and surfing sportswear, as well as team uniforms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sportswear Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling eyeglasses with darkened lenses that reduce the amount of sunlight reaching the eyes, often used as fashion accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sunglass Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling attire for swimming and surfing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Swimwear Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in making, repairing or altering clothing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tailor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A facility that uses fluorescent lamps or devices that emit ultraviolet radiation to produce a cosmetic tan for customers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tanning Salon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A facility where customers are given permanent and decorative tattoos and body piercings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tattoo Parlor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all textiles. These are the material made from fiber, that are woven, felted, or knitted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Textile

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.textile to the mso:fashion.fiber that is a part of the textile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fiber

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:fashion.textile to the mso:fashion.weave that is used in the type of textile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weave

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling uniforms for businesses, for military and academic institutions, and/or for athletic teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uniform Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in fixing and adjusting timepieces that are worn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Watch Repair

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all weaves, These are the patterns of weave used to create cloth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weave

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a pattern of weaving fibers with a textile that instantiates this pattern.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Textiles of this Weave

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fashion weeks. These are the industry events to show designers' latest collections.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fashion Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling garments designed for women. Includes stores that sell accessories (hats, purses, scarves, and umbrellas), bridal wear, casual wear, lingerie, underwear, maternity clothing, special sizes (petite, taller, and plus sizes), suits, dresses, and swimwear.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Women's Clothing Store
